text: Relevant Regulations / General Regulations / : This document regulates the use of facilities and information resources under the management of the University's Information and Library Center to serve readers' learning and research needs.
Relevant Regulations / General Regulations / : These regulations apply to all individuals and organizations using library services, as well as all staff and employees working at the Library.

Relevant Regulations / Use of the Traditional Library / Regulations on Library Cards and Their Use / Khoan 1a: Student, trainee, or postgraduate cards issued by university units, integrated with library access functions.
Relevant Regulations / Use of the Traditional Library / Regulations on Library Cards and Their Use / Khoan 1b: Library-issued cards for readers who do not have multifunctional cards.

Relevant Regulations / Use of the Traditional Library / Regulations on Library Cards and Their Use / Khoan 2: Library cards must not be lent or used by others. Cardholders are responsible for all materials borrowed using their cards.

Relevant Regulations / Use of the Traditional Library / Regulations on Library Cards and Their Use / Khoan 3: The validity of multifunctional cards corresponds to the learners study duration; library-issued cards are valid for 6 months and may be extended when necessary.
Relevant Regulations / Use of the Traditional Library / Reading Room Regulations / Khoan 1: Readers must present a valid card and store personal belongings before entering the reading room.
Relevant Regulations / Use of the Traditional Library / Reading Room Regulations / Khoan 2: Readers may retrieve materials from shelves themselves but must not take them out of the reading room.

Relevant Regulations / Use of the Traditional Library / Reading Room Regulations / Khoan 3: Readers must not change the position of materials or take more than two books or one type of newspaper or magazine at a time.
Relevant Regulations / Use of the Traditional Library / Reading Room Regulations / Khoan 4: Group discussions must be conducted at an appropriate volume without causing noise disturbance.
Relevant Regulations / Use of the Traditional Library / Reading Room Regulations / Khoan 5: Before leaving, readers must return the ticket and locker key and retrieve their library card.
Relevant Regulations / Use of the Traditional Library / Borrowing and Returning Regulations / Khoan 1: Materials allowed for home borrowing include textbooks and reference materials.
Relevant Regulations / Use of the Traditional Library / Borrowing and Returning Regulations / Khoan 2: The maximum number of borrowed items depends on the reader category.
Relevant Regulations / Use of the Traditional Library / Borrowing and Returning Regulations / Khoan 3: Deposit policies are implemented in accordance with university regulations.
Relevant Regulations / Use of the Traditional Library / Borrowing and Returning Regulations / Khoan 4: Readers must check the condition of materials before borrowing.

Relevant Regulations / Use of the Traditional Library / Borrowing and Returning Regulations / Khoan 5: Extensions must be requested when needed; late returns or lost books are handled according to regulations.
Relevant Regulations / Use of the Traditional Library / Security, Safety, and Preservation / Khoan 1: Prohibited substances and flammable or explosive materials are not allowed in the Library.
Relevant Regulations / Use of the Traditional Library / Security, Safety, and Preservation / Khoan 2: Readers are not allowed to install or modify library computers without permission.

Relevant Regulations / Use of the Traditional Library / Security, Safety, and Preservation / Khoan 3: Readers are responsible for preserving library materials and property and must comply with inspections when required.

Relevant Regulations / Use of the Traditional Library / Security, Safety, and Preservation / Khoan 4: Before graduation, withdrawal, or job transfer, all borrowed materials must be returned and any penalties settled.
Relevant Regulations / Use of the Traditional Library / Intellectual Property Law / Khoan 1: Readers must comply with intellectual property laws when using library materials.
Relevant Regulations / Use of the Traditional Library / Intellectual Property Law / Khoan 2: Unauthorized copying of library materials is prohibited.
Relevant Regulations / Use of the Traditional Library / Workplace Culture / Khoan 1: Readers must maintain proper workplace culture, dress appropriately, and keep shared spaces clean.
Relevant Regulations / Use of the Traditional Library / Workplace Culture / Khoan 2: Accessing inappropriate or harmful online content is prohibited.
Relevant Regulations / Use of the Traditional Library / Workplace Culture / Khoan 3: Writing, drawing, or placing feet on tables and chairs is not allowed.
Relevant Regulations / Use of the Digital Library / : Readers may access available digital resources on the library website.
Relevant Regulations / Use of the Digital Library / : Readers must comply with copyright and intellectual property regulations when using digital resources.
Relevant Regulations / Implementation Provisions / : The Library encourages and rewards readers who actively and responsibly use library services.
Relevant Regulations / Implementation Provisions / Handling of Violations / Khoan 1: Lending cards or removing materials from the reading room results in suspension of library services for one month.
Relevant Regulations / Implementation Provisions / Handling of Violations / Khoan 2: Causing noise or unsanitary conditions may result in suspension from one week to one month.
Relevant Regulations / Implementation Provisions / Handling of Violations / Khoan 3: Damaging library materials or property requires compensation in accordance with regulations.
Relevant Regulations / Implementation Provisions / Handling of Violations / Khoan 4: Serious violations are handled in accordance with institutional regulations and the law.
Relevant Regulations / Implementation Provisions / : These regulations take effect from the date of issuance and may be amended when necessary.
